---
import Image from "astro/components/Image.astro";
import AvatarSvg from "@/assets/avatar.svg";
import RootLayout from "@/layouts/root-layout.astro";
---

<RootLayout title="About Torben Haack">
  <header>
    <hgroup>
      <h1>Torben Haack</h1>
      <p>Software Engineer | IT Specialist, Data & Process Analysis</p>
    </hgroup>
    <Image src={AvatarSvg} alt="Torben Haack" width={200} height={200} />
  </header>
  <main>
    <section>
      <p>
        I build scalable, maintainable software for Mercedes-Benz Digital
        Factory Campus. My focus: streamlining workflows, delivering robust
        platforms, and driving technical excellence.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Experience</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Start</th>
            <th>End</th>
            <th>Company</th>
            <th>Role & Impact</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><time datetime="2025-01">2025-01</time></td>
            <td><span>Present</span></td>
            <td>Mercedes-Benz</td>
            <td
              >Engineering scalable platforms, data solutions, and developer
              tooling for global teams</td
            >
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><time datetime="2022-09">2022-09</time></td>
            <td><time datetime="2025-01">2025-01</time></td>
            <td>Mercedes-Benz</td>
            <td
              >IT Specialist Apprenticeship (Data & Process Analysis) —
              Graduated 6 months early; highest exam grade (1.4) in Berlin for
              this profession in IHK Exam Winter 24/25</td
            >
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><time datetime="2021-07">2021-07</time></td>
            <td><time datetime="2022-09">2022-09</time></td>
            <td>&mdash;</td>
            <td>
              Transition period: relocated to Berlin and focused on independent
              software projects, including Warp-Themes and a HAFAS station
              monitor.
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>&mdash;</td>
            <td><time datetime="2021-07">2021-07</time></td>
            <td>Secondary School</td>
            <td>A-levels (Social Studies), Grade: 2.8</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Mentored new apprentices and led workshops on development best
          practices and Git.
        </li>
        <li>Delivered measurable value to multiple projects from day one.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Core Skills</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Software architecture, design patterns, and maintainable code</li>
        <li>Technical decision-making for long-term project success</li>
        <li>
          DevOps: CI/CD automation, version control, cloud-native strategies
        </li>
        <li>Proficient in TypeScript, Next.js, Python, Docker, Git, Azure</li>
        <li>Continuous learning and rapid adaptation to new technologies</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Selected Projects</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>MYP – Manage Your Printer (2025):</strong> Enterprise-grade printer
          management system (Next.js, TypeScript). SSO, RBAC, analytics, Podman deployment.
          Delivered insights and seamless integration for department-wide operations.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>PromptLab (2024):</strong> Modular prompt engineering tool (React,
          Radix UI, Tailwind CSS). Live previews, dynamic inputs, custom template
          interpreter. Explored generative UI and modern web capabilities.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Warp-Themes (2022):</strong> Web-based theme builder for Warp Terminal
          and VS Code. YAML-driven UI, VS Code extension, Bash scripting. Enabled
          easy theme creation and cross-platform sync.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Early Projects:</strong> Minecraft plugin development (Java, PHP),
          3D school exploration site (JavaScript, Canvas). Built foundational skills
          and a passion for software engineering.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Approach & Values</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Results-driven: Deliver measurable impact and ROI</li>
        <li>Collaboration: Mentor, lead, and empower teams</li>
        <li>Curiosity: Embrace new challenges and continuous growth</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</RootLayout>

<style>
  hgroup h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing);
  }
  hgroup p {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-tx-2);
  }

  header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: row;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  header img {
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  main {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  main p:first-child {
    max-width: 70%;
    color: var(--color-tx-1);
  }
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
  thead th {
    background: var(--color-ui);
    color: var(--color-tx-2);
    font-weight: var(--font-semibold);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-ui-2);
    text-align: left;
    letter-spacing: var(--letter-spacing);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
  tbody td {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-ui-3);
    color: var(--color-tx);
    background: var(--color-bg);
    vertical-align: top;
  }
  tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }
  tbody tr {
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }
  tbody tr:hover {
    background: var(--color-ui-2);
  }
  time {
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
</style>
